  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the economy as apparently legitimate income\n\nMost legal definitions include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origins of criminally derived funds\n- Attempting to disguise the true ownership or source of funds\n- Engaging in financial transactions designed to hide illegal proceeds\n- Transferring money to avoid reporting requirements\n\nSpecific details and penalties differ by country, but most developed nations have anti-money laundering (AML) laws criminalizing such activities.",
